Jeff Wicks, News24FILE: Around one thousand people on average die on SA roads every month. (Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash;&nbsp;Two boys riding their bicycles on Circle Drive in Pinetown were badly injured after being struck by a car on Saturday. ER24 spokesperson, Werner Vermaak, said that the boys, aged 11 and 12-years-old, may have been dragged under the car after it hit them. "At approximately 13:00, paramedics arrived on the scene where they found the two boys seated in a nearby taxi," he said. &ldquo;It is understood that they were riding their bicycles when they fell and a car collided with them. One of the boys sustained several burns and abrasions. The other sustained a severe laceration to his head and a possible fractured arm," Vermaak said. The taxi driver, who happened on the scene of the accident soon after it happened, helped the injured boys into his taxi and called paramedics. &ldquo;Paramedics treated both the boys and transported them to RK Khan Hospital for further treatment. The driver of the vehicle was in shock about what had happened,&rdquo; he said.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.